==Demographics==
{{Expand section|date=February 2023}}
With 95 residents and a typical age of 27.1 in 2020, Cedar, Michigan had a median family income of $43,750. The population of Cedar, Michigan decreased from 106 to 95 between 2019 and 2020, a 10.4% decrease, and its median household income increased from $43,750 to $57,500, a 31.4% increase between 2020 and 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Cedar Demographics - Get Current Census Data for Cedar, MI |url=https://www.michigan-demographics.com/cedar-demographics |access-date=2023-02-15 |website=www.michigan-demographics.com}}</ref>

